{k \choose n} = \frac{k}{n}{k-1\choose n-1} = \left(\frac{k}{n} -1\right){k-1\choose n-1} + {k-1\choose n-1}
 {k \choose n} = \left(\frac{k}{n} -1\right){k-1\choose n-1} + \frac{k-1}{n-1}{k-2 \choose n-2} 
 {k \choose n} = \left[\sum_{i=1}^{M-1} \left(\frac{k-i+1}{n-i+1} - 1 \right){k-i \choose n -i}\right] + \frac{k-M+1}{n-M+1}{k-M \choose n-M}
